wikipedia_page.main: Gavin Richard Haynes (born 29 September 1969 in Wordsley, Stourbridge) is a retired professional  cricketer who played for Worcestershire from 1991 to 1999. Haynes now coaches Dudley District Cricket club and plays for Ombersley C.C.

response: The son of the cricketer Gavin Haynes, he was born at Kidderminster in February 1999. He was educated at Malvern College, before going up to the University of Leeds. While studying at Leeds, he played two first-class cricket matches for Leeds/Bradford MCCU against Derbyshire and Yorkshire in 2019. He scored 38 runs in his two matches with a high score of 20, while with slow left-arm orthodox bowling, he took 4 wickets with best figures of 3 for 37. His brother, Jack, plays county cricket for Worcestershire.
